lines.text: it's easier not to be wise
and measure these things by your brains
i sank into eden with you
alone in the church by and by
i'll read to you here save your eyes
you'll need them your boat is at sea
and the greatest of teachers won't hesitate
to leave you there by yourself
i alone love you fear is not the end of this
i alone love you, i alone tempt you
we long to be here by his resolve
alone in the church by and by
to cradle the baby in space
and leave you there by yourself
fear is not the end of this
oh, now we took it back too far
only love can save us now
all the riddles that you burn
all come running back to you
all these rhythms that you hide
only the love can save us now
all these riddles that you burn
i alone tempt you, i alone love you
fear is not the end of this
